= Literature

The below literature is only a subset of the research papers and books that are relevant to the topic. If you are familiar with a reference that you think is important to the topic of mixture approximations, please add it to the below list.

== Distributed time delays (mixture approximations)

T.K.S. Ritschel, 2025. On Erlang Mixture Approximations for Differential Equations with Distributed Time Delays. arXiv: [http://arxiv.org/abs/2502.12984 2502.12984]. DOI (code): [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15685296 10.5281/zenodo.15685296]. In submission.

N. Guglielmi and E. Hairer, 2025. Applying stiff integrators for ordinary differential equations and delay differential equations to problems with distributed delays, SIAM Journal on Scientific Computing, 47, pp. A102–A123. DOI: [https://doi.org/10.1137/24M1632413 10.1137/24M1632413].

T.K.S. Ritschel, J. Wyller, 2025. An Algorithm for Distributed Time Delay Identification without A Priori Knowledge of the Kernel. Automatica 178, pp. 112382. arXiv: [https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.07328 2405.07328]. DOI (code): [https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10001583 10.5281\/zenodo.10001583]. DOI: [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.automatica.2025.112382 10.1016/j.automatica.2025.112382].

